snippet.textDisplay: I read a lot of the comments below and I don't care to argue with anyone, having said that, I think khabib is going to maul Tony.  In a lot of the comments below, people cite that tony has destroyed his opponents so on and so forth, but these people fail to realize that khabib's style isn't conducive to destroying people.  He basically rag dolls his opponents to the point that they're exhausted or too hurt to pose a serious threat back.  Like when he fought dustin, dustin was bloodied a bit but the man was done at the end, did u guys see how khabib basically raked his face with his hand to put the choke on, dustin couldn't do anything at that point in the fight.  The man was simply defeated.  All fighters are tired at the end of a 25 minute fight, but the exhaustion is much different when a fighter has to basically support his own weight and that of khabib on his back for the majority of the rounds.  When khabib has a hold of someone, his first priority is to counter the movement of the other fighter so as to maintain control, once that is done then its ground and pound.  But even the first part, which is maintaining control, is an effective weapon because the other guy wastes his energy carrying khabib while also trying to fight back/get away.  Now tony has great cardio, but there is a difference between having stamina from moving/throwing punches to carrying someone and getting hit while doing so.  I watched a video where barbosa picked tony to win, lol, I find it amusing that he did so, considering the fact that khabib made him look like an amateur when they fought, he got completely rag dolled.  I also read below a lot abt tony's magical elbows, all i can say is k!  When he fought conor and he had him on the ground and he was talking to dana while trying to break conor's arm, conor landed a hard illegal knee right to khabib's face and the man simply put his head down and carried on.
